# Azure Ethos guardrails

Source of truth: `docs/DESIGN.md`

## Colors

- Brand colors: `#1313ec` (ethos-blue) and `#fdfbf7` (ethos-cream). No others.
- Use Tailwind tokens (`text-ethos-blue`, `bg-ethos-cream`), not raw hex in components.

## Typography

- Serif: Newsreader — display, headlines, titles, body.
- Sans: Inter — labels, utility text, navigation.
- No other fonts.

## Spacing

- `macro` (160px) between major sections.
- Use `SITE_CONTENT_SHELL` from `lib/site-layout.ts` for horizontal framing.

## Elevation

- No box-shadows on cards or sections.
- No rounded corners exceeding 10px (except brand-defined circles).
- No 1px borders for general layout. Use hairline blue or tonal shifts only.
- Shadows (if required): atmospheric only — `0 20px 40px rgba(19,19,236,0.05)`.

## Interaction

- Hover: `#1313ec` site-wide. Do not add opacity-based hover on primary links.
- Image hover: grayscale-to-color + `1.03x` scale.

## Lab Vault exception

- `/lab` uses a **full-dark Vault** aesthetic (including header and footer chrome) via `app/lab/layout.tsx`.
- Dark ground replaces `bg-ethos-cream`; text flips to cream/white; `ethos-blue` remains the accent.
- Azure Halo is hidden or dimmed on Lab.
- All other pages (Index, Ethos, Selected Work, Doodles, Contact) remain cream-forward.
- See `docs/DECISIONS.md` "Lab page (full-dark Vault)" for the canonical rule.
